Elderly men, women and widows in Ikoyi Obalende Local Council Development Area (LCDA) of Lagos State have received financial support from a councillor, Mr. Sulaiman Jubril. The donation was done under a programme tagged: “Financial support for elders, men and women”. It was the second edition. Fifty beneficiaries went home with N5,000 each. Three got N20,000 for medical treatment. Speaking at the event, Jubril, the councillor representing Ward ‘A’, said the programme was his little way of contributing to the development of his community.   